In the mood for Thai so thought I would stop in for the first time. Pretty small place and not many people inside. Bad indication for a Saturday night. I tried my favorite, Chicken with Yellow Curry. Service was pretty quick. They brought a decent sized entree with white rice. The broth of the curry although flavorful, was too watery. Curry should be thicker not soupy. The chicken seemed over cooked or just poor quality or not very fresh. It was not very tender and a bit on the dry side. Won't be coming back.

